article.headline: Air Force 73, N.C. Central 56
article.story: AIR FORCE ACADEMY, Colo. -- Evan Washington had 15 points and eight rebounds to lead Air Force to a 73-56 victory over North Carolina Central on Saturday night. Taylor Broekhuis added 14 points and seven rebounds for the Falcons (6-2). Tom Fow and Taylor Stewart had 10 points each for Air Force, which won its fourth straight home game. The Falcons held the Eagles (4-4) to 35 percent shooting. C.J. Wilkerson led the Eagles with 18 points. David Best had 12 and Landon Clement 10. North Carolina Central had its three-game winning streak snapped. The Eagles have lost 44 of their last 45 road games.
